%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22348%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Katherine%20McLaughlin.%3Cp%3EAli%20Barfield%20at%20Wild%20We%20Wander%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20have%20loved%20saving%20since%20I%20was%20a%20kid%2C%20but%20it%20became%20an%20unhealthy%20compulsion%20for%20me.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAfter%20years%20of%20denying%20myself%2C%20I%20experienced%20%26quot%3Bfrugality%20fatigue%26quot%3B%20and%20went%20on%20a%20splurging%20binge.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20added%20fun%20spending%20and%20a%20weekly%20treat%20to%20my%20budget%20so%20I%20don't%20feel%20deprived.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20created%20a%20savings%20plan%2C%20I%20was%208%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20an%20iPod%20Shuffle.%20I%20needed%20%24100%20to%20make%20the%20purchase%2C%20so%20I%20saved%20my%20%245%20allowance%20each%20week%20until%20I%20finally%20had%20the%20magic%20amount.%20I%20still%20remember%20the%20day%20my%20dad%20took%20me%20to%20Best%20Buy%20and%20I%20emptied%20my%20entire%20piggy%20bank%20%E2%80%94%20one%20%245%20bill%20at%20a%20time%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20checkout%20counter%20and%20walked%20away%20with%20my%20new%20iPod.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20shaped%20the%20way%20I%20managed%20my%20money%20for%20years.%20Having%20control%20over%20my%20money%20was%20thrilling%2C%20and%20I%20loved%20the%20idea%20that%20I%20could%20save%20and%20budget%20to%20get%20the%20things%20I%20wanted.%20As%20I%20grew%20older%20and%20started%20earning%20more%20money%2C%20being%20%26quot%3Ba%20saver%26quot%3B%20became%20a%20part%20of%20my%20identity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20over%20time%2C%20being%20frugal%20turned%20into%20a%20compulsion.%20Almost%20like%20a%20game%20with%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20how%20little%20could%20I%20actually%20spend%20while%20still%20ensuring%20I%20had%20the%20necessities%3F%20I%20was%20always%20looking%20for%20the%20cheaper%20option%2C%20I%20never%20bought%20anything%20%26quot%3Bjust%20for%20fun%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20rarely%20ate%20out%2C%20and%20I'd%20often%20miss%20out%20on%20events%20with%20friends%20just%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20spend%20the%20money%20to%20participate.%20While%20frugality%20is%20certainly%20not%20a%20bad%20trait%20to%20have%2C%20I%20took%20it%20to%20such%20an%20extreme%20level%20that%20I%20wasn't%20enjoying%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20money%20I%20earned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20no%20longer%20controlling%20money%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20letting%20it%20control%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrugality%20fatigue%20led%20to%20overspending%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20I%20was%20experiencing%20%26quot%3Bfrugality%20fatigue.%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20term%20used%20by%20some%20sociologists%20to%20describe%20budgeting%20burnout.%20Essentially%2C%20being%20so%20frugal%20for%20so%20long%20that%20it%20becomes%20too%20hard%20to%20keep%20up%20with%2C%20eventually%20leading%20to%20financial%20breakdown%20and%20frivolous%20overspending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20so%20many%20things%20in%20life%20%E2%80%94%20dieting%20and%20working%20out%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few%20%E2%80%94%20going%20%26quot%3Ball%20in%26quot%3B%20all%20at%20once%20is%20unsustainable%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20I%20got%20tired%20of%20watching%20my%20bank%20statements%20and%20denying%20myself%20the%20things%20I%20wanted.%20Doing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20right%20thing%26quot%3B%20all%20the%20time%20was%20getting%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20happen%20all%20at%20once%2C%20but%20slowly%2C%20my%20budget%20disappeared.%20One%20purchase%20here%2C%20another%20there.%20Giving%20in%20felt%20so%20good.%20If%20I%20wanted%20something%2C%20I%20bought%20it.%20For%20about%20six%20months%2C%20I%20was%20on%20a%20complete%20splurging%20spree.%20I%20bought%20clothes%2C%20expensive%20tech%20gear%2C%20furniture%2C%20anything%20I%20could%20get%20my%20hands%20on.%20Luckily%2C%20I%20never%20spent%20money%20I%20didn't%20have%2C%20but%20I%20dipped%20into%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20my%20savings%20account%20and%20lost%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20where%20I%20could%20have%20been%20adding%20to%20my%20wealth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20now%20been%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20spectrum%3A%20extreme%20saving%20and%20extreme%20spending.%20Neither%20worked.%20I%20knew%20I%20needed%20to%20find%20balance%20and%20a%20way%20to%20ensure%20I%20was%20still%20hitting%20my%20savings%20goals%20while%20also%20living%20my%20life%20in%20an%20enjoyable%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-no-penalty-cds%5C%22%3Ebest%20no-penalty%20CDs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20good%20way%20to%20lock%20in%20higher%20rates%20on%20CDs%20without%20facing%20penalties%20if%20you%20need%20to%20withdraw%20funds%20before%20the%20maturity%20date.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fcit-bank-cd-rates%5C%22%3ECIT%20Bank%20CD%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fraisin-review%5C%22%3ERaisin%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20popular%20no-penalty%20CD%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20made%202%20important%20changes%20to%20my%20budget%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20to%20avoiding%20frugality%20fatigue%20comes%20in%20allowing%20small%20splurges%20or%20occasional%20unnecessary%20spending.%20So%20I%20took%20a%20few%20steps%20to%20become%20a%20happier%2C%20more%20sustainable%20saver.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20I%20added%20'fun%20spending'%20to%20my%20budget%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20my%20mindset%20switch%2C%20I%20felt%20guilty%20about%20buying%20things%20for%20myself.%20But%20after%20my%20bout%20with%20frugality%20fatigue%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20loosen%20some%20of%20the%20restrictions%20I'd%20put%20in%20place%20or%20I'd%20just%20burn%20out%20again.%20So%2C%20I%20added%20%26quot%3Bfun%20spending%26quot%3B%20into%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebudgeting%20app%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20set%20aside%20about%20%2450%20per%20paycheck%20to%20use%20however%20I%20want.%20Sometimes%20that%20means%20ordering%20dinner%20instead%20of%20making%20it%20at%20home%2C%20or%20buying%20a%20new%20book%20instead%20of%20visiting%20the%20library.%20Other%20times%2C%20I'll%20keep%20the%20money%20aside%20for%20future%20purchases%20that%20are%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20was%20anxious%20that%20using%20this%20money%20might%20make%20me%20relapse%20into%20overspending.%20However%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20it's%20actually%20extremely%20important%20for%20my%20long-term%20goals.%20I've%20come%20to%20think%20of%20it%20as%20analogous%20to%20resting%20when%20I'm%20trying%20to%20be%20productive.%20It's%20impossible%20to%20work%20hard%20over%20long%20periods%20of%20time%20if%20I'm%20never%20taking%20the%20time%20to%20relax%20and%20recharge.%20It's%20the%20same%20with%20saving.%20It's%20very%20hard%20to%20be%20a%20good%20saver%20if%20I%20never%20allow%20myself%20to%20enjoy%20what%20saving%20can%20do%20for%20me.%20Spending%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20money%20has%20become%20integral%20to%20saving%20large%20amounts%20of%20money%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBudgeting%20can%20feel%20restrictive%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20just%20a%20tool.%20By%20creating%20space%20to%20indulge%2C%20I%20know%20I'm%20still%20putting%20aside%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20disposable%20income%20and%20working%20toward%20my%20savings%20goals%2C%20but%20I'm%20having%20fun%20on%20the%20journey%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20I%20get%20myself%20a%20treat%20every%20week%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20big%20reasons%20I%20experienced%20frugality%20fatigue%20was%20because%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20never%20had%20anything%20to%20look%20forward%20to.%20While%20I%20knew%20hitting%20certain%20savings%20milestones%20would%20feel%20good%2C%20the%20day-to-day%20grind%20became%20tiresome%20when%20every%20week%20felt%20the%20same%20and%20the%20payoff%20felt%20so%20far%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20I%20implement%20%26quot%3Bmini-splurges%26quot%3B%20once%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20Fridays%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20way%20to%20treat%20myself%20and%20give%20me%20something%20to%20get%20excited%20about%20each%20week.%20Usually%2C%20this%20looks%20like%20buying%20myself%20a%20nice%20latte%20and%20taking%20a%20walk%20around%20my%20neighborhood.%20Or%2C%20pre-pandemic%2C%20meeting%20up%20with%20a%20friend%20at%20a%20coffee%20shop.%20While%20it's%20definitely%20cheaper%20to%20make%20coffee%20at%20home%2C%20splurging%20on%20a%20%245%20craft%20cup%20feels%20special%20without%20really%20being%20that%20expensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20finding%20ways%20to%20integrate%20enjoyable%20spending%20back%20into%20my%20week%2C%20I%20finally%20feel%20like%20I'm%20in%20a%20happy%20and%20sustainable%20routine.%20I'm%20living%20below%20my%20means%2C%20but%20I'm%20still%20enjoying%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20January%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpinching-pennies-wealth-building-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1723752602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60004edba8de7700187d3cef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpinching-pennies-wealth-building-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22She%20was%20extremely%20frugal%20for%20years%2C%20to%20the%20point%20that%20she%20denied%20herself%20any%20fun.%20That%20led%20to%20extreme%20overspending%20%E2%80%94%20so%20she%20had%20to%20make%20a%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20McLaughlin)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C